events.title: Evening Unfolds: A Snapshot of the 10th of November
Convoy Sets Sail for Bougie: GLENFINLAS Leads the Charge
events.description: 78. At 1700 10th November, the slow assault convoy sailed for Bougie, consisting of the M.T. ships GLENFINLAS | (Commodore), STANHILL, URLANA, and OCEAN

events.title: Oil Tanker DEWDALE Sets Sail from Algiers with H.M.S. MULL Escorting to Bougie
events.description: 79. The oiler DEWDALE left Algiers at 1800 10th November, having been delayed by oiling ships) H.M.S. MULL of the slow assault convoy escort remained behind to escort her to Bougie. DEWDALE and MULL
